Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Definition", "TechNoteSection",
 CellID->1122958171,ExpressionUUID->"39022943-ec68-499a-bcb6-b48b438aa4ba"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In classical information, entropy is concerned with random variables. \
Suppose that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["X", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "dd3f1c70-d05c-4460-97e2-4ba4b6944ff0"],
 " is a random variable taking a value from a discrete set ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"{", "x", "}"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1004dbf2-dc16-47e9-8a2f-747bf07e134e"],
 ". The value of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["X", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0f7af505-78d1-41dd-bb40-8df6f708f051"],
 " is not fixed but determined randomly by a probability distribution, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"p", 
    RowBox[{"(", "x", ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6a0cd7cb-c328-4607-bb6c-b1190a2eed09"],
 ". Intuitively, the uncertainty in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["X", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "81f5afc2-f6a1-434e-a6f4-a0542f8ab839"],
 " is lower if the probability distribution has a narrow peak at a particular \
value ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["x", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9de14ea3-b26b-4eaf-aae2-4ec227cf9bb4"],
 ". For example, consider a binary case ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0", ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f9da6bb9-6882-4831-a917-86d4c2e49b3a"],
 ". When ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"p", "(", "0", ")"}], "=", "1"}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"bdb773d4-97c6-4635-b57a-4fdcdd51aa4a"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"p", "(", "1", ")"}], "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"f4a7dbda-4327-4455-960a-6c75a1c5a029"],
 ", we know the value of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["X", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a2df421c-8de6-4a6d-8ea8-38b4a54d973d"],
 " with certainty. In this case, there is no uncertainty at all. On the \
contrary, the uncertainty is high when the probability is broadly \
distributed. For example, in the binary case, if ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"p", "(", "0", ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"p", "(", "1", ")"}], "=", 
     RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d020e24d-62d7-49dd-8566-0728e65fa74d"],
 ", it is hard to guess the value of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["X", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "87b02dd0-30df-48de-b4c6-7b49bdcfa58e"],
 ". The uncertainty is maximum in this case."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->2095287155,ExpressionUUID->"9ce0bcfa-75cc-482a-8de9-6dc1ac744d5e"],

Cell["\<\
To quantify such a tendency of the uncertainty in a random variable, we \
define the entropy by\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1270584561,ExpressionUUID->"58e1f067-9ea2-4df0-94de-f7b22d2bae4b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"H", "(", "X", ")"}], "\[Congruent]", 
     RowBox[{"H", "(", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"p", "(", "x", ")"}], "}"}], ")"}]}], ":=", 
    RowBox[{"-", 
     RowBox[{
      UnderscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", "x"], 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"p", "(", "x", ")"}], "log", " ", 
       RowBox[{"p", "(", "x", ")"}]}]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a7946a1b-10b2-4d04-b453-a29aeba017ef"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->993262308,ExpressionUUID->"3e7ffd46-9cd3-4ff7-9db2-26c3b48a4c0a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "It is called the ",
 StyleBox["Shannon entropy",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " associated with the probability distribution ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"p", 
     RowBox[{"(", "x", ")"}]}], "}"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ae13119e-c42d-4e3f-97ba-497ab890daa5"],
 ". The logarithm concerning entropies is taken to base 2. When ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"p", "(", "x", ")"}], "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"e9a9b5ef-32de-46aa-bdfc-b4c9c401d4ee"],
 " for some values ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["x", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "785efcc9-c226-4221-aa4e-068995f3a8e2"],
 ", then the logarithm alone is ill-defined. However, the function ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"x", " ", "log", " ", "x"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c5eaf555-53a8-49ed-8496-31d5e5df0460"],
 " converges to 0, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"x", " ", "log", " ", "x"}], " ", "\[RightArrow]", " ", 
    SuperscriptBox["0", "-"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4a98a9d0-fa9e-4633-8425-21398a0d4e45"],
 ", as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"x", "\[RightArrow]", 
    SuperscriptBox["0", "+"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bb58fc68-2805-44f0-a70b-354e154da091"],
 ". We thus ",
 StyleBox["define",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"0", "log0"}], "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "80ff0bd6-f285-4fe2-9064-0173189f96be"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->231393651,ExpressionUUID->"dd425268-6285-45f3-ba43-2050f89dff0e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The entropy is associated with the probability distribution rather than a \
particular random variable or the indices of the values. In this respect, the \
notation ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"H", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"p", 
       RowBox[{"(", "x", ")"}]}], "}"}], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"381c4e1a-d056-4ac6-9a67-1a5740a21c9f"],
 " is more appropriate than ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"H", 
    RowBox[{"(", "X", ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e75c9a43-a301-4424-9bbb-f1c176970d0b"],
 ". Nevertheless, for notational convenience, we will often use both \
notations interchangeably. The Shannon entropy defined above puts the \
foundation of all variants of entropy. Every variant of entropy is \
conceptually equivalent to the above definition."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1542993249,ExpressionUUID->"7dc540e5-4967-4ed2-ad26-a742950f54b2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To check whether the above definition reflects the expected tendency of \
uncertainty, consider again the binary random variable with the value set ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0", ",", "1"}], "}"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "628d1f1f-e30e-4217-b80b-cae6b6168c59"],
 ". Let ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"p", "(", "0", ")"}], "=", "p"}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"e080c312-97c9-4685-a3f4-479d8085b8e9"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"p", "(", "1", ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"1", "\[Minus]", "p"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "00cca210-ed83-49c6-bc38-f3151ea27576"],
 ". ",
 ButtonBox["Figure 1",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/ShannonEntropy#1166102292"],
 " shows the Shannon entropy ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"H", " ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"p", ",", 
       RowBox[{"1", "\[Minus]", "p"}]}], "}"}], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"819721b4-740f-4648-9ef9-9391bcc1ea2a"],
 " as a function of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["p", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "dd676062-6d7a-4ec8-aae2-6a56a4efa187"],
 ". We observe that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"H", "(", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"0", ",", "1"}], "}"}], ")"}], "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"75fe7748-79a8-4e74-9588-6bcfeddcdd09"],
 ". It is consistent because ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"X", "=", "1"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e53b8c7b-34ef-44cb-a66d-1a7b627b1ff1"],
 " with certainty in this case. Similarly, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"H", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"1", ",", "0"}], "}"}], ")"}]}], "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"60e8923e-19cc-4514-9966-87f6371382ef"],
 " because in this case ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"X", "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "12b32b1b-09c5-41d2-9271-64e588818679"],
 " without ambiguity. On the other hand, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"H", " ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"p", ",", 
       RowBox[{"1", "\[Minus]", "p"}]}], "}"}], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"af655ce9-6803-4350-b96c-e38d3e419b77"],
 " has the maximum log 2 at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"p", "=", 
    RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4e99e8d2-7a46-4d7f-8497-3f87711ae6bf"],
 ". This is also consistent with our expectation because ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"p", "=", 
    RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e1f36750-8d24-4b10-8d38-d819cd2b123c"],
 " is the most uncertain situation."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->447581990,ExpressionUUID->"834f224c-6a8e-47e8-8232-78403e74e897"],

