Cell["\t", "TechNoteText",
 TabFilling->"\[LongDash]\[NegativeThickSpace]",
 TabSpacings->Scaled[1],
 FontColor->GrayLevel[0.85],
 CellID->1727452194,ExpressionUUID->"c37bf314-5e30-4a25-9b7b-8486466746c7"],

Cell["\<\
There are many more interesting and useful properties of entropies and mutual \
information. Here, we have kept the discussion minimal. Interested readers \
may refer to Wehrl (1978).\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1457600765,ExpressionUUID->"bf85ee15-1726-4c58-92c4-cfbf7a1c3a00"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Data Compression", "TechNoteSection",
 CellID->1128673029,ExpressionUUID->"fe83b8ce-f866-4918-aff6-bfeb318eb747"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "As an example of application of the Shannon entropy, let us consider a \
problem of data compression. Suppose that we have a binary string of of \
length ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["n", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "33b66609-9d77-42a8-af14-29b18bd688c1"],
 ","
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->884544452,ExpressionUUID->"0055fe91-6507-48e6-8f40-4596c1e593ac"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["x", "1"], 
    SubscriptBox["x", "2"], 
    SubscriptBox["\[Ellipsis]x", "n"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f451ca08-6f3a-42a1-990c-fbab65f1d6a1"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1656800230,ExpressionUUID->"4a352673-875e-4f2f-8329-2e5e0a391f30"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "with each \[OpenCurlyQuote]character\[CloseCurlyQuote] ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["x", "k"], "\[Element]", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"0", ",", "1"}], "}"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1e70823e-4a6d-4e29-a9de-7892f5cc2244"],
 ". Is it possible to compress the string into a shorter string that still \
carries the same information? If it is the case, one can save the physical \
resource, say, to store the message."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1568498608,ExpressionUUID->"5af83102-0fc3-482b-9b2a-5baffd2c9edc"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To mathematically model the problem, we regard each character ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["x", "k"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b452472c-25d8-4494-9f98-5af12fe0b228"],
 " for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"k", "=", "1"}], ",", "2", ",", "\[Ellipsis]", ",", "n"}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"c81acd7f-0c86-4b71-aff0-d818f9c0ba86"],
 " as a realization of a random variable ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["X", "k"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b385d84e-cf85-4007-b3bd-f036df8ecaed"],
 ". We assume that the random variables ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["X", "k"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e1b57de9-ea55-49d7-b91e-c490823516c7"],
 " are statistically independent and identically distributed with the \
probabilities ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"p", "(", "0", ")"}], "=", "p"}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"a682fa71-d27f-4618-b08a-bb361744b8a2"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"p", "(", "1", ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"1", "\[Minus]", "p"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fcfce32c-1504-4bb3-842c-ae14f7541ef4"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1394337731,ExpressionUUID->"58d7c086-84ee-4d37-9a7a-18258dcc0b48"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The basic idea to compress the message is to classify strings into typical \
and atypical strings. For large ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["n", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fda5d9f2-e71f-4ee7-83cf-bf7e9829c1e2"],
 ", a string such as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"00", "\[Ellipsis]", " ", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "804ceaff-caf8-4bdc-9cbe-922d995b844c"],
 " or ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"11", "\[Ellipsis]1"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6808d84f-6547-49f9-abc0-b55247414566"],
 " is highly unlikely, and we regard it atypical. Typical strings contain, on \
average, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"n", "\[VeryThinSpace]", "p"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "08d4a675-f8bd-46e4-922e-fd7b8f88c0f3"],
 " 0s and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"n", "(", 
    RowBox[{"1", "\[Minus]", "p"}], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "269ff439-def8-4e71-929d-a6247b6ccb42"],
 " 1s. We do not need to store every string of characters. We only store \
typical strings. The probability for an actual string to be atypical vanishes \
for large ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["n", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0592386d-4db0-4940-89bc-f1a6aa1f78a8"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1292688853,ExpressionUUID->"1b691851-dee5-48c2-89ba-00467ac9f082"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "How many distinct typical strings are there then? Before we estimate the \
number ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["N", "typical"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5acc635f-2e1b-411d-8382-e9c32666c082"],
 " of such strings, we first calculate the probability ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"p", "(", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["x", "1"], ",", 
     SubscriptBox["x", "2"], ",", "\[Ellipsis]", " ", ",", 
     SubscriptBox["x", "n"]}], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9c5f3696-dd35-4180-8d24-53ff20bd48f1"],
 " for a particular typical string ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["x", "1"], 
    SubscriptBox["x", "2"], 
    SubscriptBox["\[Ellipsis]x", "n"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1933b8aa-995c-4703-ae5f-63cf560d1ffa"],
 ". Since the characters are independent and identically distributed,"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->129495672,ExpressionUUID->"d8e04937-1aa0-4890-bcfc-53ad92898db5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"p", "(", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["x", "1"], ",", "\[Ellipsis]", " ", ",", 
      SubscriptBox["x", "n"]}], ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"p", "(", 
       SubscriptBox["x", "1"], ")"}], 
      RowBox[{"p", "(", 
       SubscriptBox["x", "2"], ")"}], 
      RowBox[{"\[Ellipsis]p", "(", 
       SubscriptBox["x", "n"], ")"}]}], "\[TildeTilde]", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["p", 
        RowBox[{"n", "\[VeryThinSpace]", "p"}]], "(", 
       RowBox[{"1", "-", "p"}], ")"}], 
      RowBox[{"n", "\[VeryThinSpace]", "(", 
       RowBox[{"1", "-", "p"}], ")"}]]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "44569b3f-504f-4761-9b83-8e25e374c797"],
 " ,"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1032824893,ExpressionUUID->"0ccec322-474d-45c9-a9e0-6ddc1d005a62"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "as long as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["x", "1"], 
    SubscriptBox["x", "2"], 
    SubscriptBox["\[Ellipsis]x", "n"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9c882bba-adc7-4578-a95c-167c41ef5122"],
 " is a typical string. We observe that the probabilities to get different \
typical strings are uniform, independent of the string. This implies that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["N", "typical"], "=", 
    RowBox[{"1", "/", 
     RowBox[{"p", "(", 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["x", "1"], ",", 
       SubscriptBox["x", "2"], ",", "\[Ellipsis]", ",", 
       SubscriptBox["x", "n"]}], ")"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "beaa9d62-0cc1-40c6-9107-5b4a9f57024e"],
 ". From the above equation, we then have"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->577657950,ExpressionUUID->"69f2054e-dbc2-46df-99db-145540fb23c8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"log", "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
      SubscriptBox["N", "typical"]}], "\[TildeTilde]", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "log"}], "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
      RowBox[{"p", "(", 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["x", "1"], ",", 
        SubscriptBox["x", "2"], ",", "\[Ellipsis]", ",", 
        SubscriptBox["x", "n"]}], ")"}]}]}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"n", "[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "p"}], "\[VeryThinSpace]", "logp"}], "-", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{"1", "-", "p"}], ")"}], 
        RowBox[{"log", "(", 
         RowBox[{"1", "-", "p"}], ")"}]}]}], "]"}], "=", 
     RowBox[{"n", "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
      RowBox[{"H", "(", 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"p", ",", 
         RowBox[{"1", "-", "p"}]}], "}"}], ")"}]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"3fca1e4f-6849-47d6-bd93-8d6cb74d0440"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->2071081210,ExpressionUUID->"3b05db65-aef2-4d44-ad2a-3a850a987298"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In short, there are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["2", 
    RowBox[{"n", "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
     RowBox[{"H", "(", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"p", ",", 
        RowBox[{"1", "\[Minus]", "p"}]}], "}"}], ")"}]}]], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"305f3d0f-4a18-4c97-a341-24e41fc74b94"],
 " typical strings. This implies that we only need ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"n", "\[VeryThinSpace]", "H", " ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"p", ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{"1", " ", "\[Minus]", " ", "p"}]}], "}"}], ")"}]}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"ec99b055-eb5c-4d92-a8c2-1effa950f361"],
 " bits to store ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["n", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "64a5442d-9e0a-457d-9c01-1d175dab03ec"],
 "-bit strings. We save ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"n", "[", 
    RowBox[{"1", "\[Minus]", 
     RowBox[{"H", " ", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"p", ",", 
         RowBox[{"1", "\[Minus]", "p"}]}], "}"}], ")"}]}]}], "]"}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"c7fed245-118e-4afe-b3a5-41f96bd8bd64"],
 " bits. This is what Shannon\[CloseCurlyQuote]s ",
 StyleBox["noiseless coding theorem",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " essentially states."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->99462247,ExpressionUUID->"7ab9d2a7-b644-40fb-8d4f-14f857c89a48"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In the above argument, we have considered binary strings. It can be easily \
extended for an alphabet of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["d", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a8569ed3-bda8-4a27-aa78-d310d9e0564e"],
 " characters, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["c", "1"], ",", 
     SubscriptBox["c", "2"], ",", "\[Ellipsis]", " ", ",", 
     SubscriptBox["c", "d"]}], "}"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "88f49deb-9bb2-4766-a610-8af7e5586334"],
 ". The random variables modeling different characters are statistically \
independent and governed by the same probability distribution ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"p", 
        RowBox[{"(", "x", ")"}]}], " ", ":", " ", "x"}], " ", "=", " ", 
      SubscriptBox["c", "2"]}], ",", 
     SubscriptBox["c", "2"], ",", "\[Ellipsis]", ",", 
     SubscriptBox["c", "d"]}], "}"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8402806f-4975-40c3-a241-2484f3ff8541"],
 ". Typical strings contain ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"n", "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
    RowBox[{"p", "(", "x", ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cb497ea3-3914-4276-b3e7-1ae574f093ff"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["x", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ea7a9649-af18-478b-8227-52979ffb2c64"],
 "s for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"x", "=", 
     SubscriptBox["c", "1"]}], ",", 
    SubscriptBox["c", "2"], ",", "\[Ellipsis]", " ", ",", 
    SubscriptBox["c", "d"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7705fd8a-fd1e-44e1-b419-19c928d2a8d2"],
 ". The probability for a particular string is then given by"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->919707963,ExpressionUUID->"f60469f4-48fc-4f00-9dd2-9897d4bbf8b9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"p", "(", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["x", "1"], ",", 
      SubscriptBox["x", "2"], ",", "\[Ellipsis]", ",", 
      SubscriptBox["x", "n"]}], ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      UnderoverscriptBox["\[CapitalPi]", 
       RowBox[{"k", "=", "1"}], "n"], 
      RowBox[{"p", "(", 
       SubscriptBox["x", "k"], ")"}]}], "\[TildeTilde]", 
     RowBox[{
      UnderoverscriptBox["\[CapitalPi]", 
       RowBox[{"x", "=", 
        SubscriptBox["c", "1"]}], 
       SubscriptBox["c", "d"]], 
      SuperscriptBox[
       RowBox[{"p", "(", "x", ")"}], 
       RowBox[{"n", "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
        RowBox[{"p", "(", "x", ")"}]}]]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"d8d4a706-4021-46a2-ba80-832b409cd03a"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->2091926682,ExpressionUUID->"48e07029-0ad1-4a49-9ffc-0f3cf4e7ffc2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "as long as the string ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["x", "1"], 
    SubscriptBox["x", "2"], 
    SubscriptBox["\[Ellipsis]x", "n"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e336d70e-ab16-46fa-a271-3070629058db"],
 " is typical. Therefore, we have"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->409475690,ExpressionUUID->"c5ad3fcd-b4f3-40b0-8fd2-c71d6db15589"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"log", "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
     SubscriptBox["N", "typical"]}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "log"}], "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
      RowBox[{"p", "(", 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["x", "1"], ",", 
        SubscriptBox["x", "2"], ",", "\[Ellipsis]", ",", 
        SubscriptBox["x", "n"]}], ")"}]}], "=", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"-", "n"}], 
       UnderscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", "x"], 
       RowBox[{"p", "(", "x", ")"}], "log", "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
       RowBox[{"p", "(", "x", ")"}]}], "=", 
      RowBox[{"n", "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
       RowBox[{"H", "(", 
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{"p", "(", "x", ")"}], "}"}], ")"}]}]}]}]}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"a2f78f0d-73f7-4cf6-a908-16a96ebc602b"],
 " ."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1520316842,ExpressionUUID->"7168ec24-4c11-4752-88bb-a1b40036696b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This implies that we need a physical resource to store only ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["2", 
    RowBox[{"n", "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
     RowBox[{"H", "(", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"p", "(", "x", ")"}], "}"}], ")"}]}]], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"e6acc89e-0f92-420e-a385-d9a430af51b1"],
 " instead of\nall ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["d", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "076d246e-c5fd-44e6-a88f-12891ebfe4d4"],
 " strings."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1204731488,ExpressionUUID->"2d836494-1a83-4f00-b39f-5be4d8e7c9b1"]
}, Open  ]],

